                <tr><!-- InstanceBeginEditable name="title" --> 
                  <td align="left" class="maintitle"><strong>Ray&rsquo;s  new novel is a hit</strong></td>
                  <!-- InstanceEndEditable --></tr>
                <tr> 
                  <td align="left" class="bodytext">&nbsp; </td>
                </tr>
                <tr> <!-- InstanceBeginEditable name="main text" --> 
                  <td align="left" valign="top" class="bodytext"> <table width="100%"  border="0" cellspacing="2" cellpadding="2">
                    <tr>
                      <td width="13%" height="81"><p class="indexbodytext"><img src="images/Writer-RayFrench.jpg" alt="Ray French" width="110" height="110"><br>                    
                        </p>                       </td>
                      <td width="87%" valign="middle" class="bodytext style1"><p>Leeds Trinity Academic Writer in Residence Ray  French has received rave reviews for his latest work <em>Going Under, </em>including an  impressive write up in <a href="http://books.guardian.co.uk/review/story/0,,1999544,00.html">The Guardian</a><em>.</em></p>                        </td>
                    </tr>
                  </table>                    
                  <p>The  book, which is Ray&rsquo;s second novel, takes a gritty look at the modern day  reality of life in a small Welsh town. The main character, Aidan, is widowed  and lives alone, with little to live or fight for. Until, that is, he is made  redundant and decides to make a dramatic protest against his predicament.</p>
                  <p><em>Going Under</em> has attracted  screenplay proposals and Ray is currently in talks to adapt it for the radio. Of  his recent acclaim, he said, &ldquo;Whenever a new book comes out I try not to think  about what kind of reviews it&rsquo;ll get as it&rsquo;s just beyond your control. However this  has taken a huge weight off my shoulders and is a massive confidence booster.&rdquo;</p>
                  <p>There  will be the opportunity to hear Ray give a reading from <em>Going Under</em> at the <a href="http://www.leedstrinity.ac.uk/events/21-3-07-writers.html">Leeds Trinity Writers&rsquo; Festival</a> on March 21st.                  </p>
                  <p>Ray  French is one of three Academic Writers in Residence funded by the Royal  Literary Fund at Leeds Trinity. The writers assist students with formatting and  writing essays and appointments for this service can be made by contacting Karen Scott on 0113 283 7445 or <a href="mailto:k.scott@leedstrinity.ac.uk"><strong>k.scott@leedstrinity.ac.uk</strong></a> <br>
  &nbsp;<br>
                    Read the <a href="http://books.guardian.co.uk/review/story/0,,1999544,00.html">Guardian&rsquo;s review  of <em>Going Under &ndash; </em>on sale now</a><br>
  <strong><a href="http://books.guardian.co.uk/review/story/0,,1999544,00.html"></a></strong></p>
                  <p>&nbsp;</p>
                  <p><a href="#top">top</a><br>
                  </p>                  </td>
